Proposed caption: The C-LARA-2 manual segmentation phase-2 editor. A
structure-only notice states that source text is read-only and that the
reviewer may edit only token boundaries by inserting or removing `|'
separators. The screen shows the text hash, a current page/segment boundary
preview, the original Page 1/Segment 1 French text (``Je t'aime,'' dit-il.),
an editable tokenisation field, and a `Save phase 2 manual segmentation'
control. This constrained interface makes boundary corrections auditable while
preventing accidental changes to source content.
